---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Expertise"
  description="Systems integration, workflow software, AI automation, and hands-on technical leadership for operations-heavy businesses."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gh-green">Expertise</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg sm:text-5xl">
      Practical systems work for operations-heavy teams
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-gh-fg-muted">
      I focus on businesses where work gets stuck between systems, inboxes, and documents.
      The goal is straightforward: fewer manual handoffs, faster response times, and more
      reliable operations on top of Google Cloud.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {[
        'Logistics / Freight / 3PL',
        'Distribution / Wholesale',
        'Construction / Trades',
        'Insurance (Agencies / Brokers)',
        'Manufacturing / Industrial',
        'Accounting / Bookkeeping',
        'Property Management',
      ].map(industry => (
        <span class="rounded-full border border-gh-border bg-white px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-gh-fg">
          {industry}
        </span>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 01: Systems Integration -->
  <section id="integration" class="py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:items-start">
        <div>
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-gh-border">01</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">
            Systems Integration
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base font-medium text-gh-green">
            Stop re-entering the same information across tools.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            I connect ERP, CRM, email, and document systems so data moves automatically instead of
            relying on batch jobs, spreadsheets, or manual updates. The result is cleaner handoffs,
            fewer mistakes, and less operational drag.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2">
            {[
              'ERP, CRM, and email integration',
              'Workflow automation triggered by real business events',
              'Google Workspace automation for Gmail, Drive, Sheets, and Calendar',
              'APIs and data pipelines that keep systems in sync',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
                <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-gh-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gh-border border-l-4 border-l-gh-green bg-white p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gh-fg-subtle">Why it matters</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">Owner:</span> Your team stops copy-pasting between systems — data flows automatically
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">CTO:</span> Integrations are designed to be observable, maintainable, and production-safe
            </li>
            <li class="pb-0">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">COO:</span> Orders stop falling through cracks, response times drop, errors disappear
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 02: Custom Software Development -->
  <section id="development" class="border-t border-gh-border bg-gh-canvas-subtle py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:items-start">
        <div class="order-1 sm:order-2">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-gh-border">02</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">
            Custom Software Development
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base font-medium text-gh-green">
            Build the missing software your workflow depends on.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            When your business needs a portal, internal tool, workflow app, or customer-facing
            system, I can take it from architecture through production deployment. One person owns
            the outcome end-to-end instead of handing work across multiple teams.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2">
            {[
              'Backend services and API development',
              'Modern frontends for internal and external workflows',
              'Cloud infrastructure and deployment automation',
              'CI/CD pipelines that support fast, reliable releases',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
                <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-gh-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="order-2 sm:order-1 rounded-2xl border border-gh-border border-l-4 border-l-gh-green bg-white p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gh-fg-subtle">Why it matters</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">Owner:</span> One person ships the whole product — backend, frontend, deployment
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">CTO:</span> The system is built with clean boundaries, deployment discipline, and room to grow
            </li>
            <li class="pb-0">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">COO:</span> Faster releases, fewer handoffs, less coordination overhead
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 03: AI & Automation -->
  <section id="ai" class="py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:items-start">
        <div>
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-gh-border">03</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">
            AI-Powered Automation
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base font-medium text-gh-green">
            Use AI where it removes real manual work.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            I build AI systems for document intake, inbox triage, knowledge lookup, and other
            repetitive tasks where speed matters but accuracy still needs guardrails. The emphasis
            is on production reliability, grounded answers, and clear failure behavior.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2">
            {[
              'LLM agent development and orchestration',
              'Knowledge base search with source-grounded responses',
              'Document classification and extraction workflows',
              'AI integrations built to fail safely instead of bluffing',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
                <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-gh-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gh-border border-l-4 border-l-gh-green bg-white p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gh-fg-subtle">Why it matters</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">Owner:</span> AI handles routine work — your team focuses on what matters
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">CTO:</span> AI systems are grounded, observable, and designed for production use
            </li>
            <li class="pb-0">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">COO:</span> Customer response times drop, processing errors disappear
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 04: Technical Leadership -->
  <section id="leadership" class="border-t border-gh-border bg-gh-canvas-subtle py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <div class="grid gap-12 sm:grid-cols-2 sm:items-start">
        <div class="order-1 sm:order-2">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold text-gh-border">04</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">
            Technical Leadership
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base font-medium text-gh-green">
            Add senior technical direction without adding distance from the work.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gh-fg-muted">
            I help teams make better technical decisions, simplify delivery, and put stronger
            operational practices in place. Because I stay hands-on, planning and execution stay
            tightly connected.
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2">
            {[
              'Technical leadership and mentorship',
              'Architecture and delivery decision-making',
              'Automation-first engineering practices',
              'Cross-functional execution with product and operations teams',
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
                <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-gh-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="order-2 sm:order-1 rounded-2xl border border-gh-border border-l-4 border-l-gh-green bg-white p-8">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gh-fg-subtle">Why it matters</p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-gh-fg-muted">
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">Owner:</span> You get a technical leader who writes code every day
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-gh-border pb-3">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">CTO:</span> You get a senior peer who can own execution in a focused part of the stack
            </li>
            <li class="pb-0">
              <span class="font-medium text-gh-fg">COO:</span> Engineering teams ship faster with clear direction and automation
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="border-t border-gh-border py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gh-fg">
        Have a workflow that breaks between systems?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gh-fg-muted">
        Book a call and we can map the process, the bottleneck, and the best first automation to ship.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kborovik"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-gh-blue px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-gh-blue-hover"
        >
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20.5 2h-17A1.5 1.5 0 002 3.5v17A1.5 1.5 0 003.5 22h17a1.5 1.5 0 001.5-1.5v-17A1.5 1.5 0 0020.5 2zM8 19H5v-9h3zM6.5 8.25A1.75 1.75 0 118.3 6.5a1.78 1.78 0 01-1.8 1.75zM19 19h-3v-4.74c0-1.42-.6-1.93-1.38-1.93A1.74 1.74 0 0013 14.19a.66.66 0 000 .14V19h-3v-9h2.9v1.3a3.11 3.11 0 012.7-1.4c1.55 0 3.36.86 3.36 3.66z" /></svg>
          LinkedIn
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://calendar.app.google/cYM3H3TsHsequR587"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-gh-green px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-gh-green-hover"
        >
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M19 4h-1V2h-2v2H8V2H6v2H5c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h14c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V6c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H5V10h14v10zm0-12H5V6h14v2zM7 12h5v5H7v-5z"/></svg>
          Book a Call
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
